<div align="left" class="article_text">

<!--startscanning--><p><font style="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#333333">V</font>anguard is looking to do some interior decorating with art from its potential players! The winning artwork will be put into the game for players to view at their leisure, most likely as a painting in a public area. The winner will also receive a spot in Vanguard’s first public beta!</p>
<p>The official rules are at the end of the post but here's a brief run down:</p>
<p><strong>1.</strong> <a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse</a> version of the contest has two stages. In the first stage, artwork is submitted to <a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse</a> and all Safehouse forum members will get to choose our finalist. The finalist is then sent on to <a href="http://www.vanguardsoh.com">Vanguard</a>.&nbsp; The winner of the contest will be chosen from among the finalists by a panel of judges comprised of <a href="http://www.sigilgames.com">Sigil Games Online</a> Team members. Judging will be based on originality, creativity, technique and style.</p>
<p><strong>2. </strong>Artwork must be original.</p>
<p><strong>3.</strong> Submissions must be in .tga or .bmp format and at least 1024 x 1024</p>
<p><strong>4.</strong> You should keep in mind that the winning piece will be placed in <a href="http://www.vanguardsoh.com">Vanguard</a> - most likely as a painting displayed in a place of prominance. So the winning piece must fit the setting. So a painting of a spaceship or an anime piece will not win, as they will not fit into the world being created by the Vangaurd team.</p>
<p><strong>5.</strong> Send in your entries to <a href="mailto:staff@thesafehouse.org">staff@thesafehouse.org</a>. Give us both your Safehouse Forums board name and your <a href="http://www.vanguardsoh.com">Vanguard</a> Forums board name. You must be a registered member of the <a href="http://www.vanguardsoh.com">Vanguard</a> Forums to enter the contest. If you aren't a registered member of either of the forums you can sign up now, there is no cut off date.</p>
<p><strong>6.</strong> We will acknowledge your entry via email.</p>
<p><strong>7.</strong> We will unveil all entries at the same time on voting day.</p>
<p><strong>8.</strong> You can only vote once.</p>
<p><strong>Important Dates<br>Oct 14th</strong> -&nbsp; Submission Deadline / Polls Open<br><strong>Oct. 21st</strong> - Polls close, Safehouse Finalist is submitted by us to SGO<br><strong>Oct. 28th </strong>- Overall winner announced on the <a href="http://www.vanguardsoh.com">Vanguard</a> website.</p>
<blockquote dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT:0px">
<p>General Rules</p>
<p>1.&nbsp;Contestants must be registered members of the Official <a href="http://www.vanguardsoh.com">Vanguard</a> Forums ("Forums").&nbsp; All entries must be submitted and displayed under the contestant's Forum name.&nbsp; It is the contestant's responsibility to ensure that his Forum registration information is accurate and current.<br>2.&nbsp;Submissions must be emailed to any one of the Affiliated Fan Sites listed below. All submissions must be received by the Affiliated Fan Sites by midnight PST on Friday, October 14, 2005.<br>3.&nbsp;Only one entry per contestant. Contestants submitting entries to more than one Affiliated Fan Site will be disqualified.<br>4.&nbsp;The Affiliated Fan Site may determine, in its sole discretion, whether a particular submission is appropriate to be displayed to the public.&nbsp; All accepted submissions will be publicly posted on each respective Affiliated Fan Site no later than Saturday, October 15th. <br>5.&nbsp;Members of the community are invited to visit the Affiliated Fan Sites and vote for which submission they like the best.&nbsp; The public voting for the finalists will begin on Saturday, October 15th by noon PST on will close on Friday, October 21, 2005. <br>6.&nbsp;The finalist with the most votes at each Affiliated Fan Site will be submitted to <a href="http://www.sigilgames.com">Sigil Games Online</a>.&nbsp; The winner of the contest will be chosen from among the finalists by a panel of judges comprised of <a href="http://www.sigilgames.com">Sigil Games Online</a> Team members. Judging will be based on originality, creativity, technique and style. Decisions of the judges are final. All finalists must be submitted to <a href="http://www.sigilgames.com">Sigil</a> from the Affiliates by Saturday, October 22nd.<br>7.&nbsp;The winner will be announced and the winning piece displayed on the Official <a href="http://www.vanguardsoh.com">Vanguard</a> Site on October 28th, 2005.<br>8.&nbsp;Contestant may not submit an entry to a Fan Site for which he or she works or volunteers.<br>9.&nbsp;Submissions must be in .tga or .bmp format and at least 1024 x 1024<br>10.&nbsp;All material must be original. Reference in the work that would have any effect on the lore or history of the game world may be disqualified. This piece is to be an original work of art that will be displayed as such.<br>11.&nbsp;Any reference to any copyrighted name, character or place, or a real name or place, or any variation thereof is grounds for disqualification. <br>12.&nbsp;<a href="http://www.vanguardsoh.com">Vanguard</a> is a game for a wide public audience. Please keep this in mind and refrain from using unacceptable language or questionable material. The decision to reject an entry based on content deemed unacceptable will be at the sole discretion of each Fan Site Administrator and <a href="http://www.sigilgames.com">Sigil Games Online</a>. <br>13.&nbsp;<a href="http://www.sigilgames.com">Sigil Games Online</a> is not responsible for the conduct of the Fan Site Affiliates. The decisions of the Fan Sites are final.<br>14.&nbsp;Prize: The winning artwork will be put into the game for players to view at their leisure, most likely as a painting in a public area. The winner will also receive a spot in Vanguard’s first public beta. </p>
<p>The above General Rules explain the terms and conditions upon which <a href="http://www.sigilgames.com">Sigil Games Online</a> offers the Fan Art Contest.&nbsp; Your submission of any artwork to an Affiliated Fan Site constitutes your acceptance to these General Rules.&nbsp; No purchase is necessary to enter or to win.&nbsp; It is expressly understood that the Fan Art Contest is a contest of skill and not a game of chance.&nbsp; The Fan Art Contest is void where prohibited.</p></blockquote><!--/startscanning-->

